{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848588135,"sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","part":{"id":"prt_d78d0e1ba001avia5bz4iwhXZ1","messageID":"msg_d78d0bdbb001tQo3JGgoIPFdgC","sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"toolu_tool-a2994df2998141038f17fe12df6c18f2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube codebase","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure. I need to understand:\n1. The overall project structure\n2. What exists in pkg/workloadmanager directory\n3. Any existing interfaces, types, or patterns\n4. Any spec files or design documents for AR-008 Sandbox GC mechanism\n5. Go module setup and dependencies\n\nSearch thoroughly for:\n- All files in pkg/workloadmanager/\n- Any files mentioning \"sandbox\", \"GC\", \"garbage\", \"cleanup\"\n- Any spec or design documents\n- go.mod file\n- Any existing test files to understand testing patterns\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of findings including file paths and key contents.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2872f1de5ffeQ2QNFEPzGven53 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive understanding of the agentcube project. Here is my detailed summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Summary of AgentCube Project Structure\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe agentcube project is a **Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents**. The project structure is organized as follows:\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/\n├── go.mod, go.sum                          # Go module files\n├── project.md                               # Project overview\n├── .sdd_prompt.md                           # SDD prompt context\n├── changes/                                 # Change requests directory\n│   ├── AR-001/ through AR-008/              # Individual AR directories\n│       ├── spec.md, design.md, tasks.md, proposal.md, delta-spec.md\n├── pkg/                                     # Main package directory\n│   ├── workloadmanager/                     # Core workload manager module\n│   ├── common/types/                        # Common type definitions\n│   └── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/               # Kubernetes API types (CRDs)\n├── testing/                                 # Testing documentation\n├── deployment/                              # Deployment specs\n├── integrations/                            # Integration specs\n├── sandbox-orchestration/                   # Sandbox orchestration specs\n├── ci-cd/                                   # CI/CD specs\n├── session-store/, session-routing/         # Session management specs\n├── python-sdk/, cli-toolkit/, code-execution/# SDK and CLI specs\n└── idle-cleanup/                            # Idle cleanup specs\n```\n\n### 2. pkg/workloadmanager Directory Contents\n\n**File paths:**\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── garbage_collector.go         # GarbageCollector implementation (133 lines)\n├── garbage_collector_test.go    # GC tests (379 lines, 9 tests)\n├── lifecycle.go                 # SandboxLifecycleManager (175 lines)\n├── lifecycle_test.go            # Lifecycle tests\n├── store.go                     # MemoryStore implementation (147 lines)\n├── store_test.go                # Store tests\n├── types.go                     # Core interfaces and types (136 lines)\n├── types_test.go                # Types tests\n├── config.go                    # HTTP server config (27 lines)\n├── config_test.go               # Config tests\n├── defaults.go                  # Constants and defaults (53 lines)\n├── defaults_test.go             # Defaults tests\n├── server.go                    # HTTPServer (109 lines)\n├── server_test.go               # Server tests\n├── router.go                    # Router wrapper (22 lines)\n├── router_test.go               # Router tests\n├── k8s_client.go                # Kubernetes client (135 lines)\n├── k8s_client_test.go           # K8s client tests\n├── informers.go                 # Informer management (31 lines)\n├── informers_test.go            # Informers tests\n├── integration_test.go          # Integration tests\n├── doc.go                       # Package documentation\n├── handlers/\n│   ├── handler.go               # Base handler types (30 lines)\n│   ├── handler_test.go          # Handler tests\n│   ├── sandbox_delete.go        # Delete sandbox handler (113 lines)\n│   ├── sandbox_delete_test.go   # Delete tests (248 lines)\n│   └── health.go, health_test.go # Health check endpoints\n└── middleware/\n    ├── logging.go, logging_test.go  # Request logging\n    ├── cors.go, cors_test.go        # CORS handling\n    └── recovery.go, recovery_test.go # Panic recovery\n```\n\n### 3. Existing Interfaces, Types, and Patterns\n\n#### Core Interfaces (pkg/workloadmanager/types.go):\n\n```go\n// Handler interface for HTTP route registration\ntype Handler interface {\n    Register(r chi.Router)\n}\n\n// Logger interface for structured logging\ntype Logger interface {\n    Info(msg string, args ...any)\n    Error(msg string, args ...any)\n}\n\n// Store interface for sandbox metadata storage\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### Error Types (pkg/workloadmanager/types.go):\n\n```go\ntype ValidationError struct { Field string; Reason string }\ntype NotFoundError struct { Resource string; Name string }\ntype InternalError struct { Err error }\ntype ServiceUnavailableError struct { Dependency string }\ntype ConflictError struct { Resource string; Err error }\n\n// Deletion reason constants\ntype DeletionReason string\nconst (\n    DeletionReasonIdleTimeout        DeletionReason = \"IdleTimeout\"\n    DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached DeletionReason = \"MaxDurationReached\"\n    DeletionReasonUserRequest        DeletionReason = \"UserRequest\"\n)\n```\n\n#### SandboxInfo Type (pkg/common/types/sandbox.go):\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind               string\n    SandboxID          string\n    SandboxNamespace   string\n    SandboxName        string\n    Name               string\n    SessionID          string\n    CreatedAt          time.Time\n    ExpiresAt          time.Time          // TTL timestamp\n    Status             string\n    EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint\n    UserToken          string\n    ServiceAccount     string\n    ServiceAccountName string\n    LastActivity       time.Time          // Idle timeout tracking\n}\n```\n\n#### Key Patterns:\n\n1. **Constructor Pattern**: Functions like `NewGarbageCollector()`, `NewSandboxLifecycleManager()` with default fallbacks\n2. **Graceful Shutdown**: Uses `stopCh chan struct{}` and `sync.WaitGroup` for goroutine synchronization\n3. **Thread-Safe Configuration**: `sync.RWMutex` for concurrent access to configuration fields\n4. **Context Timeout Protection**: All operations wrapped with `context.WithTimeout`\n5. **Error Delegation**: Centralized `HandleError()` function for HTTP error responses\n6. **Middleware Chain**: Recovery → Logging → CORS → Handler\n\n### 4. AR-008 Sandbox GC Mechanism - Spec Files and Design Documents\n\n**File paths:**\n- `/changes/AR-008/spec.md` - Requirements specification (37 lines, placeholder)\n- `/changes/AR-008/design.md` - Detailed technical design (536 lines, **COMPLETE**)\n- `/changes/AR-008/tasks.md` - Implementation tasks (308 lines, **100% COMPLETE**)\n- `/changes/AR-008/proposal.md` - Initial proposal\n- `/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md` - Delta specification\n\n**AR-008 Status**: Implementation is **100% COMPLETE** with all 24 tasks finished.\n\n#### GarbageCollector Implementation (garbage_collector.go):\n\n```go\ntype GarbageCollector struct {\n    manager     *SandboxLifecycleManager  // Deletion delegate\n    interval    time.Duration             // GC cycle interval (default: 2m)\n    onceTimeout time.Duration             // Single cycle timeout (default: 2m)\n    stopCh      chan struct{}             // Graceful shutdown signal\n    wg          sync.WaitGroup            // Goroutine synchronization\n    logger      Logger                    // Structured logging\n    idleTimeout time.Duration             // Idle sandbox threshold (default: 15m)\n    idleMu      sync.RWMutex              // Protects idleTimeout concurrent access\n}\n\nconst GCBatchSize = 16  // Max sandboxes per GC cycle per category\n```\n\n#### Key GC Methods:\n- `Start()` - Launches background goroutine\n- `Stop()` - Graceful shutdown with WaitGroup\n- `runLoop()` - Background ticker loop\n- `runOnce(ctx)` - Single GC cycle with timeout protection\n- `SetIdleTimeout(timeout)` - Runtime configuration\n- `GetStats()` - Stats retrieval for monitoring\n\n#### GC Flow:\n1. Immediate cleanup on start, then periodic every `interval` (2m)\n2. Query expired sandboxes (`ExpiresAt < now`) - up to 16\n3. Query inactive sandboxes (`LastActivity < now - idleTimeout`) - up to 16\n4. Delete via `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox()`\n5. Ignore NotFound errors, log other errors but continue\n6. Log successful deletions with reason\n\n### 5. Go Module Setup and Dependencies\n\n**go.mod file:**\n```\nmodule github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n\ngo 1.25.7\n\nrequire (\n    github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.0.12        # HTTP router\n    github.com/stretchr/testify v1.9.0      # Testing framework\n    k8s.io/api v0.31.0                       # Kubernetes API types\n    k8s.io/apimachinery v0.31.0             # Kubernetes meta types\n    k8s.io/client-go v0.31.0                # Kubernetes client\n    sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.0  # Controller runtime\n)\n```\n\n**Indirect dependencies include:**\n- `github.com/google/uuid` - UUID generation\n- `golang.org/x/time` - Rate limiting\n- `k8s.io/klog/v2` - Kubernetes logging\n- `k8s.io/utils` - Kubernetes utilities\n- Various JSON/YAML/Protobuf serialization libraries\n\n### 6. Testing Patterns\n\n**Testing Framework**: Uses `github.com/stretchr/testify` with `assert` and `require` packages.\n\n**Test File Pattern** (from garbage_collector_test.go):\n\n```go\nfunc TestNewGarbageCollector(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup: Create fake clients\n    fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n    dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n    informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n    \n    k8sClient := &K8sClient{\n        dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n        coreClient:      fakeClient,\n        informerFactory: informerFactory,\n    }\n    \n    store := NewMemoryStore()\n    logger := &mockLogger{}\n    config := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n    \n    manager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n    gc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n    \n    // Assertions\n    assert.NotNil(t, gc)\n    assert.Equal(t, GarbageCollectorInterval, gc.interval)\n}\n```\n\n**Mock Logger Pattern**:\n```go\ntype mockLogger struct{}\nfunc (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {}\nfunc (l *mockLogger) Error(msg string, args ...any) {}\n```\n\n**Test Categories for GC**:\n- Constructor tests (default values, explicit values)\n- Lifecycle tests (Start/Stop)\n- Cleanup tests (expired, inactive, batch limit)\n- Error handling tests (NotFound, other errors)\n- Concurrent safety tests (race detection)\n- Stats retrieval tests\n\n**HTTP Handler Testing Pattern** (from sandbox_delete_test.go):\n```go\nfunc TestDeletionHandler_DeleteSuccess(t *testing.T) {\n    handler, store := setupTestHandler()\n    \n    // Create test sandbox\n    sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{...}\n    store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), sandbox)\n    \n    // Create request\n    r := chi.NewRouter()\n    r.Delete(\"/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId}\", handler.handleDeleteAgentRuntimeSandbox)\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"DELETE\", \"/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/session-123\", nil)\n    rec := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    \n    // Execute and verify\n    r.ServeHTTP(rec, req)\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, rec.Code)\n}\n```\n\n### 7. Additional Observations\n\n**Constants and Defaults (defaults.go)**:\n```go\nDefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\nDefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\nDefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour\nGarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute\nSandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second\n\n// Label keys for Kubernetes resources\nLabelKeySessionID    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\nLabelKeyWorkloadName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\nLabelKeySandboxName  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n\n// Kubernetes GVR definitions\nSandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n    Group:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n    Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n    Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n}\n```\n\n**LifecycleConfig Structure (lifecycle.go)**:\n```go\ntype LifecycleConfig struct {\n    DefaultTTL          time.Duration  // 8h\n    DefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration  // 15m\n    DefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration  // 8h\n    GCInterval          time.Duration  // 2m\n    GCOnceTimeout       time.Duration  // 2m\n    DeletionGracePeriod int64          // 0\n    DeletionTimeout     time.Duration  // 30s\n}\n```\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive summary covers all requested aspects of the agentcube project, including the overall structure, workloadmanager contents, interfaces/types/patterns, AR-008 GC specifications, Go module dependencies, and testing patterns.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2872f1de5ffeQ2QNFEPzGven53","model":{"modelID":"glm-5","providerID":"bailian-coding-plan"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube codebase","time":{"start":1775848448536,"end":1775848588133}}}}
