{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848599614,"sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","part":{"id":"prt_d78d324190017je1IxXhtvdgJW","messageID":"msg_d78d303b2001N8mEI9uMCDWfMY","sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4ba8f09f21d94d85ab286d747a3cc461","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"sync\"\n6: \t\"time\"\n7: )\n8: \n9: const GCBatchSize = 16\n10: \n11: type GarbageCollector struct {\n12: \tmanager     *SandboxLifecycleManager\n13: \tinterval    time.Duration\n14: \tonceTimeout time.Duration\n15: \tstopCh      chan struct{}\n16: \twg          sync.WaitGroup\n17: \tlogger      Logger\n18: \tidleTimeout time.Duration\n19: \tidleMu      sync.RWMutex\n20: }\n21: \n22: func NewGarbageCollector(manager *SandboxLifecycleManager, interval, onceTimeout time.Duration, logger Logger) *GarbageCollector {\n23: \tif interval == 0 {\n24: \t\tinterval = GarbageCollectorInterval\n25: \t}\n26: \tif onceTimeout == 0 {\n27: \t\tonceTimeout = 2 * time.Minute\n28: \t}\n29: \n30: \treturn &GarbageCollector{\n31: \t\tmanager:     manager,\n32: \t\tinterval:    interval,\n33: \t\tonceTimeout: onceTimeout,\n34: \t\tstopCh:      make(chan struct{}),\n35: \t\tlogger:      logger,\n36: \t\tidleTimeout: manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout,\n37: \t}\n38: }\n39: \n40: func (gc *GarbageCollector) getIdleTimeout() time.Duration {\n41: \tgc.idleMu.RLock()\n42: \tdefer gc.idleMu.RUnlock()\n43: \treturn gc.idleTimeout\n44: }\n45: \n46: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Start() {\n47: \tgc.wg.Add(1)\n48: \tgo gc.runLoop()\n49: }\n50: \n51: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop() {\n52: \tclose(gc.stopCh)\n53: \tgc.wg.Wait()\n54: }\n55: \n56: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runLoop() {\n57: \tdefer gc.wg.Done()\n58: \n59: \tticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)\n60: \tdefer ticker.Stop()\n61: \n62: \tgc.runOnce(context.Background())\n63: \n64: \tfor {\n65: \t\tselect {\n66: \t\tcase <-gc.stopCh:\n67: \t\t\tgc.logger.Info(\"garbage collector stopped\")\n68: \t\t\treturn\n69: \t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n70: \t\t\tgc.runOnce(context.Background())\n71: \t\t}\n72: \t}\n73: }\n74: \n75: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runOnce(ctx context.Context) error {\n76: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)\n77: \tdefer cancel()\n78: \n79: \tnow := time.Now()\n80: \tidleTimeout := gc.getIdleTimeout()\n81: \n82: \texpired, err := gc.manager.store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)\n83: \tif err != nil {\n84: \t\tgc.logger.Error(\"failed to list expired sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n85: \t\treturn err\n86: \t}\n87: \n88: \tinactiveBefore := now.Add(-idleTimeout)\n89: \tinactive, err := gc.manager.store.ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)\n90: \tif err != nil {\n91: \t\tgc.logger.Error(\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n92: \t\treturn err\n93: \t}\n94: \n95: \tallSandboxes := append(expired, inactive...)\n96: \n97: \tfor _, sb := range allSandboxes {\n98: \t\tif err := gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID); err != nil {\n99: \t\t\tif _, ok := err.(*NotFoundError); ok {\n100: \t\t\t\tcontinue\n101: \t\t\t}\n102: \t\t\tgc.logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\", \"sessionID\", sb.SessionID, \"err\", err)\n103: \t\t\tcontinue\n104: \t\t}\n105: \n106: \t\treason := determineDeletionReason(sb, now, idleTimeout)\n107: \t\tgc.logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", \"sessionID\", sb.SessionID, \"sandboxName\", sb.SandboxName, \"reason\", reason)\n108: \t}\n109: \n110: \treturn nil\n111: }\n112: \n113: func (gc *GarbageCollector) SetIdleTimeout(timeout time.Duration) {\n114: \tgc.idleMu.Lock()\n115: \tdefer gc.idleMu.Unlock()\n116: \tgc.idleTimeout = timeout\n117: }\n118: \n119: func (gc *GarbageCollector) GetStats() GarbageCollectorStats {\n120: \tgc.idleMu.RLock()\n121: \tdefer gc.idleMu.RUnlock()\n122: \treturn GarbageCollectorStats{\n123: \t\tInterval:    gc.interval,\n124: \t\tOnceTimeout: gc.onceTimeout,\n125: \t\tIdleTimeout: gc.idleTimeout,\n126: \t}\n127: }\n128: \n129: type GarbageCollectorStats struct {\n130: \tInterval    time.Duration\n131: \tOnceTimeout time.Duration\n132: \tIdleTimeout time.Duration\n133: }\n\n(End of file - total 133 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"sync\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\nconst GCBatchSize = 16\n\ntype GarbageCollector struct {\n\tmanager     *SandboxLifecycleManager\n\tinterval    time.Duration\n\tonceTimeout time.Duration\n\tstopCh      chan struct{}\n\twg          sync.WaitGroup\n\tlogger      Logger\n\tidleTimeout time.Duration\n\tidleMu      sync.RWMutex\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go","time":{"start":1775848599588,"end":1775848599612}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848599616,"sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","part":{"id":"prt_d78d32801001ynaaq0qCLYCbNa","messageID":"msg_d78d303b2001N8mEI9uMCDWfMY","sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-91b0b6b04bec4b908f0b87ef5339401c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"sync\"\n6: \t\"testing\"\n7: \t\"time\"\n8: \n9: \t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n10: \t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n11: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n12: \tdynamicfake \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\"\n13: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n14: \n15: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n16: )\n17: \n18: func TestNewGarbageCollector(t *testing.T) {\n19: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n20: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n21: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n22: \n23: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{\n24: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n25: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n26: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n27: \t}\n28: \n29: \tstore := NewMemoryStore()\n30: \tlogger := &mockLogger{}\n31: \tconfig := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n32: \n33: \tmanager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n34: \n35: \tgc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n36: \n37: \tassert.NotNil(t, gc)\n38: \tassert.Equal(t, GarbageCollectorInterval, gc.interval)\n39: \tassert.Equal(t, 2*time.Minute, gc.onceTimeout)\n40: }\n41: \n42: func TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval(t *testing.T) {\n43: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n44: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n45: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n46: \n47: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{\n48: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n49: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n50: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n51: \t}\n52: \n53: \tstore := NewMemoryStore()\n54: \tlogger := &mockLogger{}\n55: \tconfig := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n56: \n57: \tmanager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n58: \n59: \tgc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, 0, 0, logger)\n60: \n61: \tassert.Equal(t, GarbageCollectorInterval, gc.interval)\n62: \tassert.Equal(t, 2*time.Minute, gc.onceTimeout)\n63: }\n64: \n65: func TestGarbageCollector_StartStop(t *testing.T) {\n66: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n67: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n68: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n69: \n70: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{\n71: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n72: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n73: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n74: \t}\n75: \n76: \tstore := NewMemoryStore()\n77: \tlogger := &mockLogger{}\n78: \tconfig := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n79: \n80: \tmanager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n81: \n82: \tgc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, 100*time.Millisecond, 1*time.Second, logger)\n83: \n84: \tgc.Start()\n85: \n86: \ttime.Sleep(50 * time.Millisecond)\n87: \n88: \tgc.Stop()\n89: \n90: \tassert.True(t, true)\n91: }\n92: \n93: func TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired(t *testing.T) {\n94: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n95: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n96: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n97: \n98: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{\n99: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n100: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n101: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n102: \t}\n103: \n104: \tstore := NewMemoryStore()\n105: \tlogger := &mockLogger{}\n106: \tconfig := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n107: \n108: \tmanager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n109: \n110: \tgc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n111: \n112: \tnow := time.Now()\n113: \n114: \texpiredSandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n115: \t\tKind:             types.SandboxKind,\n116: \t\tSandboxID:        \"sandbox-expired\",\n117: \t\tSandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n118: \t\tSandboxName:      \"sandbox-expired\",\n119: \t\tSessionID:        \"session-expired\",\n120: \t\tCreatedAt:        now.Add(-10 * time.Hour),\n121: \t\tExpiresAt:        now.Add(-2 * time.Hour),\n122: \t\tStatus:           \"running\",\n123: \t}\n124: \n125: \tactiveSandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n126: \t\tKind:             types.SandboxKind,\n127: \t\tSandboxID:        \"sandbox-active\",\n128: \t\tSandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n129: \t\tSandboxName:      \"sandbox-active\",\n130: \t\tSessionID:        \"session-active\",\n131: \t\tCreatedAt:        now,\n132: \t\tExpiresAt:        now.Add(8 * time.Hour),\n133: \t\tStatus:           \"running\",\n134: \t}\n135: \n136: \terr := store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), expiredSandbox)\n137: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n138: \terr = store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), activeSandbox)\n139: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n140: \n141: \tassert.Equal(t, 2, store.Size())\n142: \n143: \terr = gc.runOnce(context.Background())\n144: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n145: \n146: \tassert.Equal(t, 1, store.Size())\n147: \n148: \t_, err = store.GetSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-expired\")\n149: \tassert.Error(t, err)\n150: \n151: \t_, err = store.GetSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-active\")\n152: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n153: }\n154: \n155: func TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive(t *testing.T) {\n156: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n157: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n158: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n159: \n160: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{\n161: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n162: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n163: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n164: \t}\n165: \n166: \tstore := NewMemoryStore()\n167: \tlogger := &mockLogger{}\n168: \tconfig := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n169: \n170: \tmanager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n171: \n172: \tgc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n173: \n174: \tnow := time.Now()\n175: \n176: \tinactiveSandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n177: \t\tKind:             types.SandboxKind,\n178: \t\tSandboxID:        \"sandbox-inactive\",\n179: \t\tSandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n180: \t\tSandboxName:      \"sandbox-inactive\",\n181: \t\tSessionID:        \"session-inactive\",\n182: \t\tCreatedAt:        now,\n183: \t\tExpiresAt:        now.Add(8 * time.Hour),\n184: \t\tLastActivity:     now.Add(-30 * time.Minute),\n185: \t\tStatus:           \"running\",\n186: \t}\n187: \n188: \tactiveSandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n189: \t\tKind:             types.SandboxKind,\n190: \t\tSandboxID:        \"sandbox-active\",\n191: \t\tSandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n192: \t\tSandboxName:      \"sandbox-active\",\n193: \t\tSessionID:        \"session-active\",\n194: \t\tCreatedAt:        now,\n195: \t\tExpiresAt:        now.Add(8 * time.Hour),\n196: \t\tLastActivity:     now,\n197: \t\tStatus:           \"running\",\n198: \t}\n199: \n200: \terr := store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), inactiveSandbox)\n201: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n202: \terr = store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), activeSandbox)\n203: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n204: \n205: \tassert.Equal(t, 2, store.Size())\n206: \n207: \terr = gc.runOnce(context.Background())\n208: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n209: \n210: \tassert.Equal(t, 1, store.Size())\n211: \n212: \t_, err = store.GetSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-inactive\")\n213: \tassert.Error(t, err)\n214: \n215: \t_, err = store.GetSandboxBySessionID(context.Background(), \"session-active\")\n216: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n217: }\n218: \n219: func TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit(t *testing.T) {\n220: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n221: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n222: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n223: \n224: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{\n225: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n226: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n227: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n228: \t}\n229: \n230: \tstore := NewMemoryStore()\n231: \tlogger := &mockLogger{}\n232: \tconfig := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n233: \n234: \tmanager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n235: \n236: \tgc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n237: \n238: \tnow := time.Now()\n239: \n240: \tfor i := 0; i < 20; i++ {\n241: \t\tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n242: \t\t\tKind:             types.SandboxKind,\n243: \t\t\tSandboxID:        \"sandbox-\" + string(rune(i)),\n244: \t\t\tSandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n245: \t\t\tSandboxName:      \"sandbox-\" + string(rune(i)),\n246: \t\t\tSessionID:        \"session-\" + string(rune(i)),\n247: \t\t\tCreatedAt:        now,\n248: \t\t\tExpiresAt:        now.Add(-1 * time.Hour),\n249: \t\t\tStatus:           \"running\",\n250: \t\t}\n251: \t\terr := store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), sandbox)\n252: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n253: \t}\n254: \n255: \tassert.Equal(t, 20, store.Size())\n256: \n257: \terr := gc.runOnce(context.Background())\n258: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n259: \n260: \tassert.LessOrEqual(t, store.Size(), 20-GCBatchSize)\n261: }\n262: \n263: func TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError(t *testing.T) {\n264: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n265: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n266: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n267: \n268: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{\n269: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n270: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n271: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n272: \t}\n273: \n274: \tstore := NewMemoryStore()\n275: \tlogger := &mockLogger{}\n276: \tconfig := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n277: \n278: \tmanager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n279: \n280: \tgc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n281: \n282: \tnow := time.Now()\n283: \n284: \tfor i := 0; i < 3; i++ {\n285: \t\tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n286: \t\t\tKind:             types.SandboxKind,\n287: \t\t\tSandboxID:        \"sandbox-\" + string(rune(i)),\n288: \t\t\tSandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n289: \t\t\tSandboxName:      \"sandbox-\" + string(rune(i)),\n290: \t\t\tSessionID:        \"session-\" + string(rune(i)),\n291: \t\t\tCreatedAt:        now,\n292: \t\t\tExpiresAt:        now.Add(-1 * time.Hour),\n293: \t\t\tStatus:           \"running\",\n294: \t\t}\n295: \t\terr := store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), sandbox)\n296: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n297: \t}\n298: \n299: \terr := gc.runOnce(context.Background())\n300: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n301: \n302: \tassert.Equal(t, 0, store.Size())\n303: }\n304: \n305: func TestGarbageCollector_GetStats(t *testing.T) {\n306: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n307: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n308: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n309: \n310: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{\n311: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n312: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n313: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n314: \t}\n315: \n316: \tstore := NewMemoryStore()\n317: \tlogger := &mockLogger{}\n318: \tconfig := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n319: \n320: \tmanager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n321: \n322: \tgc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, 5*time.Minute, 3*time.Minute, logger)\n323: \tgc.SetIdleTimeout(20 * time.Minute)\n324: \n325: \tstats := gc.GetStats()\n326: \n327: \tassert.Equal(t, 5*time.Minute, stats.Interval)\n328: \tassert.Equal(t, 3*time.Minute, stats.OnceTimeout)\n329: \tassert.Equal(t, 20*time.Minute, stats.IdleTimeout)\n330: }\n331: \n332: func TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce(t *testing.T) {\n333: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n334: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n335: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n336: \n337: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{\n338: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n339: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n340: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n341: \t}\n342: \n343: \tstore := NewMemoryStore()\n344: \tlogger := &mockLogger{}\n345: \tconfig := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n346: \n347: \tmanager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n348: \n349: \tgc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n350: \n351: \tnow := time.Now()\n352: \n353: \tfor i := 0; i < 10; i++ {\n354: \t\tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n355: \t\t\tKind:             types.SandboxKind,\n356: \t\t\tSandboxID:        \"sandbox-\" + string(rune(i)),\n357: \t\t\tSandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n358: \t\t\tSandboxName:      \"sandbox-\" + string(rune(i)),\n359: \t\t\tSessionID:        \"session-\" + string(rune(i)),\n360: \t\t\tCreatedAt:        now,\n361: \t\t\tExpiresAt:        now.Add(-1 * time.Hour),\n362: \t\t\tStatus:           \"running\",\n363: \t\t}\n364: \t\terr := store.StoreSandbox(context.Background(), sandbox)\n365: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n366: \t}\n367: \n368: \tvar wg sync.WaitGroup\n369: \tfor i := 0; i < 3; i++ {\n370: \t\twg.Add(1)\n371: \t\tgo func() {\n372: \t\t\tdefer wg.Done()\n373: \t\t\tgc.runOnce(context.Background())\n374: \t\t}()\n375: \t}\n376: \twg.Wait()\n377: \n378: \tassert.LessOrEqual(t, store.Size(), 10)\n379: }\n\n(End of file - total 379 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"sync\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n\tdynamicfake \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\nfunc TestNewGarbageCollector(t *testing.T) {\n\tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n\tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go","time":{"start":1775848599592,"end":1775848599614}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848599619,"sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","part":{"id":"prt_d78d32bf60016XdZ9P3jTiIdvo","messageID":"msg_d78d303b2001N8mEI9uMCDWfMY","sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-46c7b2fe13064b35bf0d343b1409a115","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 实现基于时间触发的 Sandbox 垃圾回收机制，自动清理过期和空闲的 Sandbox 资源，防止集群资源累积和膨胀。GC 作为后台 goroutine 运行，提供 TTL 强制执行、空闲超时清理、批量处理限制和可配置的时间间隔。\n14: \n15: ## Design\n16: \n17: ### Architecture\n18: \n19: ```\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                        HTTPServer                               │\n22: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n23: │  │                SandboxLifecycleManager                   │   │\n24: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  │   │\n25: │  │  │  K8sClient  │  │ MemoryStore  │  │ LifecycleConfig│  │   │\n26: │  │  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └────────────────┘  │   │\n27: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n28: │                           │                                     │\n29: │                           │ delegation                          │\n30: │                           ▼                                     │\n31: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n32: │  │                   GarbageCollector                       │   │\n33: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │   │\n34: │  │  │                   runLoop                          │ │   │\n35: │  │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────────┐  │ │   │\n36: │  │  │  │ time.Ticker  │──│ runOnce (per cycle)        │  │ │   │\n37: │  │  │  └──────────────┘  │ ┌────────────────────────┐ │  │ │   │\n38: │  │  │                    │ │ListExpiredSandboxes    │ │  │ │   │\n39: │  │  │                    │ │ListInactiveSandboxes   │ │  │ │   │\n40: │  │  │                    │ │DeleteSandbox (batched) │ │  │ │   │\n41: │  │  │                    │ └────────────────────────┘ │  │ │   │\n42: │  │  │                    └────────────────────────────┘  │ │   │\n43: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │   │\n44: │  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐ │   │\n45: │  │  │   Start()  │  │    Stop()       │  │ GetStats()   │ │   │\n46: │  │  └────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └──────────────┘ │   │\n47: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │   │\n48: │  │  │SetIdleTimeout() ←─ runtime config via idleMu       │ │   │\n49: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │   │\n50: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n51: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ### Component Relationships\n55: \n56: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n57: |-----------|------|--------------|\n58: | `GarbageCollector` | Periodic cleanup executor | `SandboxLifecycleManager`, `Store` |\n59: | `SandboxLifecycleManager` | Deletion delegate | `K8sClient`, `Store` |\n60: | `MemoryStore` | Sandbox metadata storage | `sync.RWMutex` |\n61: | `runLoop` | Background goroutine ticker loop | `time.Ticker`, `stopCh` |\n62: | `runOnce` | Single GC cycle logic | `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes` |\n63: \n64: ### GC Execution Flow\n65: \n66: ```\n67: Start() → wg.Add(1) → go runLoop()\n68:                             │\n69:                             ├── runOnce(ctx) [immediate]\n70:                             ├── ticker := NewTicker(interval)\n71:                             └── for {\n72:                                   select {\n73:                                     case <-stopCh: return\n74:                                     case <-ticker.C: runOnce(ctx)\n75:                                   }\n76:                                 }\n77: \n78: runOnce(ctx)\n79:   │\n80:   ├── ctx, cancel := WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)\n81:   ├── expired := ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)\n82:   ├── inactive := ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, now.Add(-idleTimeout), GCBatchSize)\n83:   └── for sb in expired + inactive:\n84:         │\n85:         ├── DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)\n86:         │     ├── GetSandboxBySessionID → NotFoundError? return\n87:         │     ├── K8sClient.Delete(SandboxGVR)\n88:         │     ├── K8sClient.Delete(SandboxClaimGVR) [if SandboxClaimKind]\n89:         │     └── Store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n90:         │\n91:         ├── NotFoundError? continue (ignore)\n92:         ├── Other error? log + continue\n93:         └── reason := determineDeletionReason(sb, now, idleTimeout)\n94:             logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", ...)\n95: \n96: Stop() → close(stopCh) → wg.Wait()\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Dependencies\n100: \n101: | Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n102: |---------|---------|-------------|\n103: | `context` | Context with timeout for GC cycles | `context` (stdlib) |\n104: | `sync` | WaitGroup, RWMutex for concurrency | `sync` (stdlib) |\n105: | `time` | Duration, Ticker, Now for timing | `time` (stdlib) |\n106: | `types` | SandboxInfo struct | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` |\n107: | `apierrors` | IsNotFound error checking | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` |\n108: | `metav1` | DeleteOptions | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` |\n109: \n110: ## Data Structures\n111: \n112: ### Core Types\n113: \n114: #### GarbageCollector Struct\n115: \n116: ```go\n117: type GarbageCollector struct {\n118:     manager     *SandboxLifecycleManager  // Deletion delegate\n119:     interval    time.Duration             // GC cycle interval (default: 2m)\n120:     onceTimeout time.Duration             // Single cycle timeout (default: 2m)\n121:     stopCh      chan struct{}             // Graceful shutdown signal\n122:     wg          sync.WaitGroup            // Goroutine synchronization\n123:     logger      Logger                    // Structured logging\n124:     idleTimeout time.Duration             // Idle sandbox threshold (default: 15m)\n125:     idleMu      sync.RWMutex              // Protects idleTimeout concurrent access\n126: }\n127: ```\n128: \n129: **Field Responsibilities:**\n130: \n131: | Field | Type | Purpose |\n132: |-------|------|---------|\n133: | `manager` | `*SandboxLifecycleManager` | Delegates `DeleteSandbox` for actual cleanup |\n134: | `interval` | `time.Duration` | Ticker interval between GC cycles |\n135: | `onceTimeout` | `time.Duration` | Context timeout for single `runOnce` execution |\n136: | `stopCh` | `chan struct{}` | Closed on `Stop()` to signal shutdown |\n137: | `wg` | `sync.WaitGroup` | Ensures goroutine completes before `Stop()` returns |\n138: | `logger` | `Logger` | Logs GC events (deletions, errors, shutdown) |\n139: | `idleTimeout` | `time.Duration` | Threshold for inactive sandbox detection |\n140: | `idleMu` | `sync.RWMutex` | Protects `idleTimeout` for runtime config changes |\n141: \n142: #### GarbageCollectorStats Struct\n143: \n144: ```go\n145: type GarbageCollectorStats struct {\n146:     Interval    time.Duration  // Current GC cycle interval\n147:     OnceTimeout time.Duration  // Current single-cycle timeout\n148:     IdleTimeout time.Duration  // Current idle threshold\n149: }\n150: ```\n151: \n152: #### Store Interface Extensions\n153: \n154: ```go\n155: type Store interface {\n156:     // ... existing methods ...\n157:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n158:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: **New Method Semantics:**\n163: \n164: | Method | Input | Output | Purpose |\n165: |--------|-------|--------|---------|\n166: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `before` timestamp, `limit` | Sandboxes with `ExpiresAt < before` | TTL-based cleanup candidates |\n167: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `before` timestamp, `limit` | Sandboxes with `LastActivity < before` | Idle timeout cleanup candidates |\n168: \n169: #### MemoryStore Implementation\n170: \n171: ```go\n172: type MemoryStore struct {\n173:     mu              sync.RWMutex\n174:     sandboxes       map[string]*types.SandboxInfo  // sessionID → SandboxInfo\n175:     expirationIndex map[string]time.Time           // sandboxID → ExpiresAt\n176: }\n177: \n178: func (s *MemoryStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(_ context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n179:     s.mu.RLock()\n180:     defer s.mu.RUnlock()\n181: \n182:     var expired []*types.SandboxInfo\n183:     for _, sandbox := range s.sandboxes {\n184:         if sandbox.ExpiresAt.Before(before) {\n185:             expired = append(expired, sandbox)\n186:         }\n187:     }\n188: \n189:     // Sort by ExpiresAt ascending (oldest first)\n190:     sort.Slice(expired, func(i, j int) bool {\n191:         return expired[i].ExpiresAt.Before(expired[j].ExpiresAt)\n192:     })\n193: \n194:     // Truncate to limit\n195:     if limit > 0 && len(expired) > limit {\n196:         expired = expired[:limit]\n197:     }\n198: \n199:     return expired, nil\n200: }\n201: \n202: func (s *MemoryStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(_ context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n203:     s.mu.RLock()\n204:     defer s.mu.RUnlock()\n205: \n206:     var inactive []*types.SandboxInfo\n207:     for _, sandbox := range s.sandboxes {\n208:         // Skip sandboxes with zero LastActivity (newly created)\n209:         if !sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero() && sandbox.LastActivity.Before(before) {\n210:             inactive = append(inactive, sandbox)\n211:         }\n212:     }\n213: \n214:     // Sort by LastActivity ascending (most inactive first)\n215:     sort.Slice(inactive, func(i, j int) bool {\n216:         return inactive[i].LastActivity.Before(inactive[j].LastActivity)\n217:     })\n218: \n219:     // Truncate to limit\n220:     if limit > 0 && len(inactive) > limit {\n221:         inactive = inactive[:limit]\n222:     }\n223: \n224:     return inactive, nil\n225: }\n226: ```\n227: \n228: #### DeletionReason Constants\n229: \n230: ```go\n231: type DeletionReason string\n232: \n233: const (\n234:     DeletionReasonIdleTimeout        DeletionReason = \"IdleTimeout\"\n235:     DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached DeletionReason = \"MaxDurationReached\"\n236:     DeletionReasonUserRequest        DeletionReason = \"UserRequest\"\n237: )\n238: ```\n239: \n240: #### LifecycleConfig GC Fields\n241: \n242: ```go\n243: type LifecycleConfig struct {\n244:     DefaultTTL          time.Duration  // Default sandbox TTL (8h)\n245:     DefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration  // Default idle threshold (15m)\n246:     DefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration  // Max session duration (8h)\n247:     GCInterval          time.Duration  // GC cycle interval (2m)\n248:     GCOnceTimeout       time.Duration  // Single GC cycle timeout (2m)\n249:     DeletionGracePeriod int64          // K8s deletion grace period (0)\n250:     DeletionTimeout     time.Duration  // Single deletion timeout (30s)\n251: }\n252: ```\n253: \n254: ### Constants\n255: \n256: ```go\n257: // pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go\n258: const (\n259:     GCBatchSize               = 16                    // Max sandboxes per GC cycle per category\n260:     GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute       // Default GC cycle interval\n261:     DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute      // Default idle timeout threshold\n262:     DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour         // Default sandbox TTL\n263:     SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second      // Single deletion timeout\n264: )\n265: ```\n266: \n267: ## API Contracts\n268: \n269: ### Constructor\n270: \n271: ```go\n272: func NewGarbageCollector(\n273:     manager *SandboxLifecycleManager,\n274:     interval time.Duration,\n275:     onceTimeout time.Duration,\n276:     logger Logger\n277: ) *GarbageCollector\n278: ```\n279: \n280: **Behavior:**\n281: - If `interval == 0`, defaults to `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2m)\n282: - If `onceTimeout == 0`, defaults to `2 * time.Minute`\n283: - Initializes `idleTimeout` from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n284: - Creates `stopCh := make(chan struct{})`\n285: \n286: ### Lifecycle Methods\n287: \n288: ```go\n289: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Start()\n290: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop()\n291: ```\n292: \n293: **Start() Contract:**\n294: - Calls `gc.wg.Add(1)`\n295: - Launches `go gc.runLoop()`\n296: - Returns immediately (non-blocking)\n297: \n298: **Stop() Contract:**\n299: - Calls `close(gc.stopCh)` to signal shutdown\n300: - Calls `gc.wg.Wait()` to block until goroutine completes\n301: - Returns only after goroutine exits\n302: \n303: ### Core Logic Methods\n304: \n305: ```go\n306: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runLoop()\n307: func (gc *GarbageCollector) runOnce(ctx context.Context) error\n308: ```\n309: \n310: **runLoop() Contract:**\n311: - Runs in separate goroutine\n312: - Executes `runOnce(ctx)` immediately on start\n313: - Creates `ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n314: - Loops on `select { <-stopCh, <-ticker.C }`\n315: - On `stopCh`, logs `\"garbage collector stopped\"` and returns\n316: - On `ticker.C`, calls `runOnce(context.Background())`\n317: - Defers `gc.wg.Done()` and `ticker.Stop()`\n318: \n319: **runOnce(ctx) Contract:**\n320: - Creates `ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)`\n321: - Returns error if `ListExpiredSandboxes` fails\n322: - Returns error if `ListInactiveSandboxes` fails\n323: - Processes at most `GCBatchSize` expired + `GCBatchSize` inactive sandboxes\n324: - Ignores `NotFoundError` (sandbox already deleted)\n325: - Logs other errors but continues processing\n326: - Logs successful deletions with reason\n327: \n328: ### Runtime Configuration Methods\n329: \n330: ```go\n331: func (gc *GarbageCollector) SetIdleTimeout(timeout time.Duration)\n332: func (gc *GarbageCollector) getIdleTimeout() time.Duration\n333: func (gc *GarbageCollector) GetStats() GarbageCollectorStats\n334: ```\n335: \n336: **SetIdleTimeout(timeout) Contract:**\n337: - Acquires `gc.idleMu.Lock()`\n338: - Updates `gc.idleTimeout`\n339: - Releases mutex\n340: \n341: **getIdleTimeout() Contract:**\n342: - Acquires `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n343: - Returns current `gc.idleTimeout`\n344: - Releases mutex\n345: \n346: **GetStats() Contract:**\n347: - Acquires `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n348: - Returns `GarbageCollectorStats{Interval, OnceTimeout, IdleTimeout}`\n349: - Releases mutex\n350: \n351: ### Helper Functions\n352: \n353: ```go\n354: func determineDeletionReason(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, now time.Time, idleTimeout time.Duration) DeletionReason\n355: ```\n356: \n357: **Contract:**\n358: - If `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`: return `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n359: - If `!sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero()` AND `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`: return `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n360: - Otherwise: return `DeletionReasonUserRequest`\n361: \n362: ## Error Handling\n363: \n364: ### Error Categories\n365: \n366: | Error Type | Source | Handling |\n367: |------------|--------|----------|\n368: | `NotFoundError` | Store lookup, K8s delete | Silently ignored (already deleted) |\n369: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` error | Store query | Logged, `runOnce` returns error |\n370: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` error | Store query | Logged, `runOnce` returns error |\n371: | `DeleteSandbox` error (non-NotFound) | Lifecycle manager | Logged, continue to next sandbox |\n372: | K8s API error | Dynamic client | Wrapped in `InternalError` or `ConflictError` |\n373: \n374: ### Error Flow\n375: \n376: ```\n377: runOnce(ctx)\n378:   │\n379:   ├── ListExpiredSandboxes returns error?\n380:   │     └── logger.Error(\"failed to list expired sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n381:   │     └── return err  [stop cycle]\n382:   │\n383:   ├── ListInactiveSandboxes returns error?\n384:   │     └── logger.Error(\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n385:   │     └── return err  [stop cycle]\n386:   │\n387:   └── for each sandbox in expired + inactive:\n388:         │\n389:         ├── DeleteSandbox returns *NotFoundError?\n390:         │     └── continue  [ignore, already deleted]\n391:         │\n392:         ├── DeleteSandbox returns other error?\n393:         │     └── logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"err\", ...)\n394:         │     └── continue  [process remaining sandboxes]\n395:         │\n396:         └── DeleteSandbox succeeds?\n397:               └── logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"sandboxName\", ..., \"reason\", ...)\n398: ```\n399: \n400: ### Timeout Handling\n401: \n402: | Timeout | Default | Purpose | Mechanism |\n403: |---------|---------|---------|-----------|\n404: | `onceTimeout` | 2m | Prevent GC cycle from hanging | `context.WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)` |\n405: | `DeletionTimeout` | 30s | Prevent single deletion from hanging | `context.WithTimeout(ctx, config.DeletionTimeout)` |\n406: | `interval` | 2m | GC cycle frequency | `time.NewTicker(interval)` |\n407: \n408: ### Graceful Degradation\n409: \n410: - GC continues processing remaining sandboxes even if some deletions fail\n411: - NotFound errors are treated as success (resource already cleaned)\n412: - List errors abort the cycle but don't crash the GC\n413: - GC restarts on next ticker cycle after errors\n414: \n415: ## Testing Strategy\n416: \n417: ### Unit Tests (garbage_collector_test.go)\n418: \n419: | Test | Scenario | Verification |\n420: |------|----------|--------------|\n421: | `TestNewGarbageCollector` | Constructor with explicit values | Fields set correctly |\n422: | `TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval` | Constructor with zero values | Defaults applied |\n423: | `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop` | Lifecycle management | Start launches goroutine, Stop waits for completion |\n424: | `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired` | Expired sandbox cleanup | Expired deleted, active remains |\n425: | `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive` | Idle timeout cleanup | Inactive deleted, active remains |\n426: | `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit` | Batch size enforcement | At most 16 deleted per category |\n427: | `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError` | Error resilience | All sandboxes processed |\n428: | `TestGarbageCollector_GetStats` | Stats retrieval | Correct values returned |\n429: | `TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce` | Concurrent safety | No race conditions |\n430: \n431: ### Test Setup Pattern\n432: \n433: ```go\n434: func setupTestGC(t *testing.T) (*GarbageCollector, *MemoryStore) {\n435:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n436:     dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n437:     informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n438: \n439:     k8sClient := &K8sClient{\n440:         dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n441:         coreClient:      fakeClient,\n442:         informerFactory: informerFactory,\n443:     }\n444: \n445:     store := NewMemoryStore()\n446:     logger := &mockLogger{}\n447:     config := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n448: \n449:     manager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n450:     gc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n451: \n452:     return gc, store\n453: }\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### Mock Logger\n457: \n458: ```go\n459: type mockLogger struct{}\n460: \n461: func (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {}\n462: func (l *mockLogger) Error(msg string, args ...any) {}\n463: ```\n464: \n465: ### Integration Tests (integration_test.go)\n466: \n467: | Test | Scenario | Verification |\n468: |------|----------|--------------|\n469: | Full GC flow | Create expired sandbox → run GC | Sandbox deleted from store and K8s |\n470: | Multiple cycles | 20+ expired sandboxes | GC processes across multiple cycles |\n471: | Lifecycle integration | Server start/stop | GC lifecycle bound to server |\n472: \n473: ### Test Coverage Goals\n474: \n475: | Area | Target Coverage |\n476: |------|------------------|\n477: | `garbage_collector.go` | >80% |\n478: | `store.go` (GC methods) | >80% |\n479: | `lifecycle.go` (`determineDeletionReason`) | 100% |\n480: \n481: ### Validation Commands\n482: \n483: ```bash\n484: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -v -run GarbageCollector\n485: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -coverprofile=coverage.out\n486: go tool cover -func=coverage.out\n487: go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager\n488: golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager\n489: ```\n490: \n491: ## Validation Checklist\n492: \n493: - [x] `GarbageCollector` struct defined with all required fields\n494: - [x] `NewGarbageCollector` constructor with default fallbacks\n495: - [x] `Start()` launches background goroutine\n496: - [x] `Stop()` signals shutdown and waits for completion\n497: - [x] `runLoop` uses ticker for periodic execution\n498: - [x] `runOnce` has context timeout protection\n499: - [x] `ListExpiredSandboxes` queries expired by `ExpiresAt`\n500: - [x] `ListInactiveSandboxes` queries inactive by `LastActivity`\n501: - [x] Batch limit (`GCBatchSize=16`) enforced per query\n502: - [x] NotFound errors silently ignored\n503: - [x] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n504: - [x] `determineDeletionReason` categorizes deletions correctly\n505: - [x] `SetIdleTimeout` runtime configuration supported\n506: - [x] `GetStats` returns current configuration\n507: - [x] `idleMu` protects concurrent `idleTimeout` access\n508: - [x] Store interface includes GC query methods\n509: - [x] `MemoryStore` implements GC query methods\n510: - [x] `LifecycleConfig` includes GC parameters\n511: - [x] `DefaultLifecycleConfig` provides GC defaults\n512: - [x] Unit tests cover expired/inactive/batch scenarios\n513: - [x] Unit tests cover concurrent safety\n514: - [x] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n515: - [x] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n516: \n517: ## Open Questions\n518: \n519: - Q: Should GC metrics be exported to Prometheus?\n520:   - A: Deferred to future enhancement. Current implementation uses structured logging only.\n521: \n522: - Q: How should distributed GC work with multiple workload-manager instances?\n523:   - A: Deferred. Leader election can be added when HA deployment is required.\n524: \n525: - Q: Should `LastActivity` be updated on heartbeat or only on user actions?\n526:   - A: Updated on user actions (sandbox creation, heartbeat API calls). The heartbeat handler updates `LastActivity`.\n527: \n528: ## References\n529: \n530: - `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Implementation\n531: - `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` - Test coverage\n532: - `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` - `DeleteSandbox` delegation, `determineDeletionReason`\n533: - `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` - `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n534: - `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Store interface, `DeletionReason` constants\n535: - `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` - Timeout constants\n536: - Kubernetes TTL Controller: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/ttlafterfinished/\n\n(End of file - total 536 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n实现基于时间触发的 Sandbox 垃圾回收机制，自动清理过期和空闲的 Sandbox 资源，防止集群资源累积和膨胀。GC 作为后台 goroutine 运行，提供 TTL 强制执行、空闲超时清理、批量处理限制和可配置的时间间隔。\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/design.md","time":{"start":1775848599594,"end":1775848599617}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848599623,"sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","part":{"id":"prt_d78d32f88001Aw9Nu6uq7xNGPy","messageID":"msg_d78d303b2001N8mEI9uMCDWfMY","sessionID":"ses_2872f4338ffegY4bVs7f3OXLR5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f8ca8c542e934770bed45e1cd0df307d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Types & Constants (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [x] **T1.1**: Define `GarbageCollectorStats` struct for stats retrieval\n20:   - Fields: `Interval`, `OnceTimeout`, `IdleTimeout`\n21:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:129-133`\n22:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n23: \n24: - [x] **T1.2**: Define GC constants in `defaults.go`\n25:   - `GarbageCollectorInterval = 2 * time.Minute`\n26:   - `GCBatchSize = 16`\n27:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:9` and `defaults.go:17`\n28:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval -v`\n29: \n30: ### Phase 2: GarbageCollector Struct & Constructor (ST-2)\n31: \n32: - [x] **T2.1**: Define `GarbageCollector` struct with all required fields\n33:   - Fields: `manager`, `interval`, `onceTimeout`, `stopCh`, `wg`, `logger`, `idleTimeout`, `idleMu`\n34:   - Thread-safe: `idleMu sync.RWMutex` protects `idleTimeout`\n35:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:11-20`\n36:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v`\n37: \n38: - [x] **T2.2**: Implement `NewGarbageCollector` constructor\n39:   - Apply defaults if `interval == 0`: use `GarbageCollectorInterval`\n40:   - Apply defaults if `onceTimeout == 0`: use `2 * time.Minute`\n41:   - Initialize `idleTimeout` from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n42:   - Create `stopCh := make(chan struct{})`\n43:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:22-38`\n44:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v && go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval -v`\n45: \n46: ### Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods (ST-3)\n47: \n48: - [x] **T3.1**: Implement `Start()` method\n49:   - Call `gc.wg.Add(1)`\n50:   - Launch `go gc.runLoop()`\n51:   - Non-blocking, returns immediately\n52:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:46-49`\n53:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v`\n54: \n55: - [x] **T3.2**: Implement `Stop()` method\n56:   - Call `close(gc.stopCh)` to signal shutdown\n57:   - Call `gc.wg.Wait()` to block until goroutine completes\n58:   - Returns only after goroutine exits\n59:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:51-54`\n60:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v`\n61: \n62: - [x] **T3.3**: Implement `runLoop()` background ticker loop\n63:   - Run in separate goroutine\n64:   - Execute `runOnce(ctx)` immediately on start\n65:   - Create `ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n66:   - Loop on `select { <-stopCh, <-ticker.C }`\n67:   - On `stopCh`: log `\"garbage collector stopped\"` and return\n68:   - On `ticker.C`: call `runOnce(context.Background())`\n69:   - Defer `gc.wg.Done()` and `ticker.Stop()`\n70:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:56-73`\n71:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v`\n72: \n73: ### Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic (ST-4)\n74: \n75: - [x] **T4.1**: Implement `runOnce(ctx)` with context timeout protection\n76:   - Create `ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)`\n77:   - Capture current time: `now := time.Now()`\n78:   - Get current `idleTimeout` via `gc.getIdleTimeout()`\n79:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:75-80`\n80:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired -v`\n81: \n82: - [x] **T4.2**: Implement expired sandbox query logic\n83:   - Call `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)`\n84:   - Log error if query fails: `\"failed to list expired sandboxes\"`\n85:   - Return error if query fails\n86:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:82-86`\n87:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired -v`\n88: \n89: - [x] **T4.3**: Implement inactive sandbox query logic\n90:   - Calculate `inactiveBefore := now.Add(-idleTimeout)`\n91:   - Call `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)`\n92:   - Log error if query fails: `\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\"`\n93:   - Return error if query fails\n94:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:88-93`\n95:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive -v`\n96: \n97: - [x] **T4.4**: Implement batch deletion loop\n98:   - Merge expired and inactive lists: `allSandboxes := append(expired, inactive...)`\n99:   - For each sandbox, call `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)`\n100:   - Handle `NotFoundError`: silently ignore (continue)\n101:   - Handle other errors: log `\"gc delete failed\"` and continue\n102:   - Log successful deletion: `\"gc deleted sandbox\"` with reason\n103:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:95-108`\n104:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError -v`\n105: \n106: - [x] **T4.5**: Implement batch size limit enforcement\n107:   - Verify at most `GCBatchSize` (16) items per category processed\n108:   - Ensure store size decreases appropriately after cleanup\n109:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:82-93` (limit param)\n110:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit -v`\n111: \n112: ### Phase 5: Runtime Configuration Methods (ST-5)\n113: \n114: - [x] **T5.1**: Implement `SetIdleTimeout(timeout)` method\n115:   - Acquire `gc.idleMu.Lock()`\n116:   - Update `gc.idleTimeout`\n117:   - Release mutex\n118:   - Thread-safe for concurrent access\n119:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:113-117`\n120:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n121: \n122: - [x] **T5.2**: Implement `getIdleTimeout()` internal method\n123:   - Acquire `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n124:   - Return current `gc.idleTimeout`\n125:   - Release mutex\n126:   - Thread-safe for concurrent reads\n127:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:40-44`\n128:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n129: \n130: - [x] **T5.3**: Implement `GetStats()` stats retrieval method\n131:   - Acquire `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n132:   - Return `GarbageCollectorStats{Interval, OnceTimeout, IdleTimeout}`\n133:   - Release mutex\n134:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:119-127`\n135:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_GetStats -v`\n136: \n137: ### Phase 6: Concurrent Safety (ST-6)\n138: \n139: - [x] **T6.1**: Implement thread-safe idleTimeout access\n140:   - Add `idleMu sync.RWMutex` to `GarbageCollector` struct\n141:   - Protect all reads/writes to `idleTimeout`\n142:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:18-20`\n143:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce -v`\n144: \n145: - [x] **T6.2**: Implement concurrent cleanup safety\n146:   - Multiple `runOnce()` calls can execute concurrently\n147:   - No race conditions on store operations\n148:   - No race conditions on idleTimeout reads\n149:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:75-111`\n150:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -race -run TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce -v`\n151: \n152: ### Phase 7: Store Integration (ST-7)\n153: \n154: - [x] **T7.1**: Add `ListExpiredSandboxes` to Store interface\n155:   - Method signature: `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n156:   - Query sandboxes where `ExpiresAt < before`\n157:   - Sort by `ExpiresAt` ascending (oldest first)\n158:   - Limit to `limit` items\n159:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go:29` and `store.go:90-110`\n160:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestListExpired -v`\n161: \n162: - [x] **T7.2**: Add `ListInactiveSandboxes` to Store interface\n163:   - Method signature: `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n164:   - Query sandboxes where `LastActivity < before` (skip zero `LastActivity`)\n165:   - Sort by `LastActivity` ascending (most inactive first)\n166:   - Limit to `limit` items\n167:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go:30` and `store.go:112-132`\n168:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestListInactive -v`\n169: \n170: - [x] **T7.3**: Implement MemoryStore GC query methods\n171:   - Use `sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe reads\n172:   - Implement sorting for deterministic cleanup order\n173:   - Implement limit truncation for batch size enforcement\n174:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go:90-132`\n175:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go -v`\n176: \n177: ### Phase 8: Deletion Reason Classification (ST-8)\n178: \n179: - [x] **T8.1**: Implement `determineDeletionReason` helper function\n180:   - If `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`: return `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n181:   - If `!sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero()` AND `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`: return `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n182:   - Otherwise: return `DeletionReasonUserRequest`\n183:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go:167-175`\n184:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go -run TestDetermineDeletionReason -v`\n185: \n186: ### Phase 9: Integration & Validation (ST-9)\n187: \n188: - [x] **T9.1**: Integrate GC with SandboxLifecycleManager\n189:   - GC delegates deletion to `manager.DeleteSandbox`\n190:   - Manager handles K8s resource deletion + store cleanup\n191:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:98`\n192:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired -v`\n193: \n194: - [x] **T9.2**: Verify error handling flow\n195:   - NotFound errors silently ignored\n196:   - List errors abort cycle but don't crash GC\n197:   - Delete errors logged but continue processing\n198:   - GC restarts on next ticker cycle after errors\n199:   - File: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go:82-108`\n200:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError -v`\n201: \n202: - [x] **T9.3**: All unit tests pass\n203:   - `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run GarbageCollector -v`\n204:   - Coverage: >80% for garbage_collector.go\n205:   - No race conditions\n206:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run GarbageCollector -v`\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## Task Dependencies\n211: \n212: ```\n213: T1.1 → T1.2\n214:   ↓\n215: T2.1 → T2.2\n216:   ↓\n217: T3.1 → T3.2 → T3.3\n218:   ↓\n219: T4.1 → T4.2 → T4.3 → T4.4 → T4.5\n220:   ↓\n221: T5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3\n222:   ↓\n223: T6.1 → T6.2\n224:   ↓\n225: T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3\n226:   ↓\n227: T8.1\n228:   ↓\n229: T9.1 → T9.2 → T9.3\n230: ```\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ## Verification Commands\n235: \n236: | Task | Verification Command |\n237: |------|----------------------|\n238: | All GC tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run GarbageCollector -v` |\n239: | Constructor tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestNewGarbageCollector -v` |\n240: | Lifecycle tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_StartStop -v` |\n241: | Cleanup tests | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector_runOnce -v` |\n242: | Concurrent safety | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -race -run TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce -v` |\n243: | Test coverage | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep garbage_collector` |\n244: | Build verification | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n245: | Lint check | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## Acceptance Criteria\n250: \n251: - [x] GarbageCollector runs as background goroutine with ticker loop\n252: - [x] Immediate cleanup on start, then periodic cleanup every `interval`\n253: - [x] Graceful shutdown via `Stop()` with `WaitGroup` synchronization\n254: - [x] Expired sandbox cleanup based on `ExpiresAt` timestamp\n255: - [x] Inactive sandbox cleanup based on `LastActivity` + `idleTimeout`\n256: - [x] Batch size limit: max 16 items per category per cycle\n257: - [x] NotFound errors silently ignored (already deleted)\n258: - [x] Other errors logged but don't stop cleanup cycle\n259: - [x] Thread-safe `idleTimeout` runtime configuration via `SetIdleTimeout`\n260: - [x] Stats retrieval via `GetStats()` for monitoring\n261: - [x] Store methods: `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n262: - [x] Deletion reason classification: `MaxDurationReached`, `IdleTimeout`, `UserRequest`\n263: - [x] All unit tests pass (9 tests)\n264: - [x] No race conditions detected\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ## Files Modified/Created\n269: \n270: | File | Status | Description |\n271: |------|--------|-------------|\n272: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | ✓ Complete | GarbageCollector implementation (133 lines) |\n273: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | ✓ Complete | Comprehensive test suite (9 tests, 379 lines) |\n274: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | ✓ Complete | Added ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes |\n275: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | ✓ Complete | Added GC methods to Store interface |\n276: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | ✓ Complete | Added determineDeletionReason helper |\n277: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | ✓ Complete | Added GarbageCollectorInterval constant |\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ## Notes\n282: \n283: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n284: - **Implementation 100% complete**\n285: - **All 9 tests pass with full coverage**\n286: - **Thread-safe implementation**: `idleMu sync.RWMutex` protects `idleTimeout` for concurrent access\n287: - **Graceful degradation**: GC continues processing even if individual deletions fail\n288: - **Batch processing**: Limit of 16 items per category prevents resource exhaustion\n289: - **Context timeout protection**: Single GC cycle limited to `onceTimeout` (default 2 minutes)\n290: - **Integration**: GC delegates deletion to `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox`\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## Implementation Timeline\n295: \n296: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n297: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n298: | Phase 1: Core Types & Constants | T1.1, T1.2 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n299: | Phase 2: Struct & Constructor | T2.1, T2.2 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n300: | Phase 3: Lifecycle Methods | T3.1, T3.2, T3.3 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n301: | Phase 4: Core Cleanup Logic | T4.1-T4.5 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n302: | Phase 5: Runtime Config | T5.1-T5.3 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n303: | Phase 6: Concurrent Safety | T6.1, T6.2 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n304: | Phase 7: Store Integration | T7.1-T7.3 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n305: | Phase 8: Deletion Reason | T8.1 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n306: | Phase 9: Integration & Validation | T9.1-T9.3 | ✓ Complete | 100% |\n307: \n308: **Total Progress: 100% Complete (24/24 tasks)**\n\n(End of file - total 308 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Types & Constants (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Define `GarbageCollectorStats` struct for stats retrieval\n  - Fields: `Interval`, `OnceTimeout`, `IdleTimeout`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775848599596,"end":1775848599620}}}}
